[~dshekhawat] I logged onto 10.104.1.211 sourced the /root/.euca/eucarc and it worked for me?
{code}
[root@odc-d-06-02 ~]# source /root/.euca/eucarc
[root@odc-d-06-02 ~]# euca-modify-property -p dns.dns_listener_address=10.104.1.211
PROPERTY	dns.dns_listener_address	10.104.1.211 was {}
[root@odc-d-06-02 ~]# euca-describe-properties dns.dns_listener_address
PROPERTY	dns.dns_listener_address	10.104.1.211
{code}

Strange ... but I think I figured the problem partially: 

I am wondering if it has to do with 2 compute services registered on my cloud ? I see the failure I pasted above has IP 10.104.1.212 in the POST request

{code}
send: 'POST /services/Properties/ HTTP/1.1\r\nAccept-Encoding: identity\r\nContent-Length: 272\r\nContent-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded; charset=UTF-8\r\nHost: 10.104.1.212\r\nUser-Agent: Boto/2.25.0 Python/2.6.6 Linux/2.6.32-431.5.1.el6.x86_64\r\n\r\n'
{code}

If I modify the EC2_URL to point to 10.104.1.212 it does not work but if I point it to 10.104.1.211 it works. Note that the setup is like this because of EUCA-8950
